Hi. Yes, I need to speak to Dr. Sagias now.

190
00:13:29,359 --> 00:13:30,694
現場是艾德裡安
It's Adrian at the site.

191
00:13:33,530 --> 00:13:34,764
手電筒? Flashlight?

192
00:13:36,967 --> 00:13:39,369
它是30,000流明
It's 30,000 lumens.

193
00:13:41,504 --> 00:13:43,274


194
00:13:43,341 --> 00:13:45,809
那是什麼嗶音？那是我
What's that beeping? That's me.

195
00:13:45,876 --> 00:13:47,878
氫含量非常高
Hydrogen levels are really high.

196
00:13:47,944 --> 00:13:49,012
危險嗎? Dangerous?

197
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,780
可能是門開的時候發生的
Probably happened when the door opened.

198
00:13:50,847 --> 00:13:52,449
是的，當氫遇到氧時
Yeah, when hydrogen meets oxygen,

199
00:13:52,515 --> 00:13:54,584
它相當具有爆炸性
it's pretty explosive.

200
00:13:54,651 --> 00:13:57,121
是的-它也製造水
Yeah-it also makes water.

201
00:13:58,455 --> 00:14:00,091
是的 Yeah.

202
00:14:03,994 --> 00:14:07,131
尼克，你不會相信剛剛發生的事
Nick, you won't believe what just happened.

203
00:14:15,438 --> 00:14:17,941
這裡沒什麼
Not much in here.

204
00:14:18,008 --> 00:14:19,876
也許我們不是第一個打開它的人
Maybe we're not the first to open it.

205
00:14:19,943 --> 00:14:23,413
不 維京人的陵墓不像埃及的陵墓
No. Viking tombs were not like Egyptian tombs.

206
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:25,448
非常基本 Very basic.

207
00:14:27,550 --> 00:14:29,619
我很驚訝它有岩石雕刻
I'm surprised it has petroglyphs.

208
00:14:29,686 --> 00:14:32,223
一定是某個特別的人
Must have been someone special.

209
00:14:32,290 --> 00:14:34,191
或者別的什麼
Or something.

210
00:14:37,627 --> 00:14:40,164
我沒有看到屍體
I don't see a body.

211
00:14:40,231 --> 00:14:42,532
維京人通常被火化
Vikings were usually cremated.

212
00:14:42,599 --> 00:14:44,968
所以這不是墳墓？
So this isn't a tomb?

213
00:14:45,035 --> 00:14:46,503
我不知道 I don't know.

214
00:14:46,569 --> 00:14:48,605
可能是個聖陵
Could be a shrine.

215
00:14:50,141 --> 00:14:52,542
符號上寫了什麼？
What did the symbols say?

216
00:14:52,609 --> 00:14:55,979
抱歉 Sorry.

217
00:14:56,046 --> 00:14:58,215
剛剛和薩吉亞斯博士談過 他不想我們在這裡
Just talked to Dr. Sagias. He doesn't want us in here.

218
00:14:58,282 --> 00:15:00,016
拜託，你現在一定在開我玩笑
Come on. You gotta be kidding me right now.

219
00:15:00,084 --> 00:15:01,451
他想派一名結構工程師
He wants to send a structural engineer

220
00:15:01,518 --> 00:15:03,520
來這裡確保它的安全
out here to make sure it's safe.

221
00:15:05,855 --> 00:15:07,224
好的 Okay.

222
00:15:08,925 --> 00:15:10,660
好的 Okay.

223
00:15:12,296 --> 00:15:13,964
來吧，格雷斯
Come on, Grace.

224
00:15:16,533 --> 00:15:17,834
知道了 Got it.

225
00:15:27,445 --> 00:15:29,546
格雷斯，來吧!
Grace, come on.

226
00:15:40,056 --> 00:15:41,958


227
00:15:46,062 --> 00:15:48,565


228
00:15:48,631 --> 00:15:50,734
肯定是挪威人
Definitely Norse.

229
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:52,535
我看到更多的狼象形文字
I see more of the wolf hieroglyphs.

230
00:15:52,602 --> 00:15:53,536
芬利爾? Fenrir?

231
00:15:53,603 --> 00:15:55,239
是的，但是...Yes, but...

232
00:15:55,306 --> 00:15:57,807
我也看到了一些美洲高山族的符號
I see some Native American symbols, too,

233
00:15:57,874 --> 00:16:00,543
比如先早 通瓦符號
like early. Tongva symbols.

234
00:16:00,610 --> 00:16:02,712
所以，這座陵墓是一個合資企業
So, this tomb was a joint venture

235
00:16:02,779 --> 00:16:05,515
界於土著部落和維京人之間？
between indigenous tribes and the Vikings?

236
00:16:05,582 --> 00:16:07,817
做個猜測，但是...
Taking a guess, but...

237
00:16:07,884 --> 00:16:09,487
也許這兩個團體都建造了這個
maybe both groups built this

238
00:16:09,552 --> 00:16:10,887
因為他們都有既定的興趣
because they both had a vested interest.

239
00:16:10,954 --> 00:16:12,922
在建造維京人陵墓？
In building a Viking tomb?

240
00:16:12,989 --> 00:16:15,058
通瓦部落為什麼要這樣做？
Why would the Tongva tribes do that?

241
00:16:15,126 --> 00:16:16,893
尊敬? Respect?

242
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,561
或者恐懼 Or fear.

243
00:16:18,628 --> 00:16:20,498
看看這些符號
Look at these symbols.

244
00:16:20,563 --> 00:16:22,632
那是瓦爾克努特，死亡的象徴
That's a Valknut, symbol of death.

245
00:16:22,699 --> 00:16:25,735
那是伊格德拉西爾，九界之樹
That's Yggdrasil, tree of the Nine Realms.

246
00:16:25,802 --> 00:16:29,140
太陽，那是壞精靈的通加語
That's Tongva for bad spirit, sun.

247
00:16:29,206 --> 00:16:31,342
也許這不是墳墓
Maybe it's not a tomb.

248
00:16:31,409 --> 00:16:33,477
也許是別的東西
Maybe it's something else.

249
00:16:33,543 --> 00:16:35,413
像是什麼？Like what?

250
00:16:35,479 --> 00:16:37,614
任何東西 Anything.

251
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:40,050
一個通道、一個房間、一個神龕
A passageway, a room, a shrine.

252
00:16:40,117 --> 00:16:41,651
一個監獄 A prison.

253
00:16:41,718 --> 00:16:43,220
為了狼神
For the wolf god

254
00:16:43,287 --> 00:16:46,357
想要吃掉太陽，摧毀九界
that wants to eat the sun and destroy the Nine Realms.

255
00:16:46,424 --> 00:16:48,092
住口 Stop.

256
00:16:48,159 --> 00:16:53,330
兩種文化合作建造監獄 為什麼？
Two cultures teaming together to build a prison. Why?

257
00:17:13,049 --> 00:17:15,685


258
00:17:37,441 --> 00:17:39,210
哇，哇! 我不這麼認為
Whoa, whoa. I don't think so.

259
00:17:39,276 --> 00:17:41,778
對不起，先生 不要碰我
Excuse me, sir. Do not touch me.

260
00:17:41,845 --> 00:17:45,116
這是一個安全區域 我們需要看一些身份證明
This is a secure area. We need to see some I.D.

261
00:17:45,182 --> 00:17:47,184
一些身份證明?
Some I.D.?

262
00:17:47,251 --> 00:17:49,752
身份證明是什麼？你不知道我是誰嗎？
What is I.D.? Do you not know who I am?

263
00:17:49,819 --> 00:17:51,155
先生，你可以是亞伯拉罕·林肯
Sir, you could be Abraham Lincoln

264
00:17:51,222 --> 00:17:52,689
和約翰·威爾克斯·布斯一起走進來
walking in here with John Wilkes Booth.

265
00:17:52,755 --> 00:17:54,858
而且我還需要身份證明
And I'd still need I.D.

266
00:17:55,959 --> 00:17:58,129
顯然是你的一些朋友
Clearly must be some friends of yours.

267
00:17:59,929 --> 00:18:02,632
你不負責，是嗎？
You're not in charge, are you?

268
00:18:02,699 --> 00:18:04,502
身份證明 I.D.

269
00:18:04,568 --> 00:18:07,071
別再提身份證明了
Enough with the I.D.

270
00:18:07,138 --> 00:18:09,440
誰負責？
Who's in charge?

271
00:18:09,507 --> 00:18:11,342
那就是尼克.薩吉亞斯博士
That'd be Dr. Nick Sagias,

272
00:18:11,408 --> 00:18:14,944
奧廷卡博物館執行主任
executive director at the Odinkar Museum.

273
00:18:15,011 --> 00:18:16,480
那個傢伙 That guy.

274
00:18:16,547 --> 00:18:18,149
薩吉亞斯博士
Dr. Sagias.

275
00:18:18,215 --> 00:18:19,716
帥哥 Handsome fellow.

276
00:18:24,555 --> 00:18:26,055
我可以進去嗎？
May I go in?

277
00:18:29,025 --> 00:18:31,362
我需要呈報這個 不，你不能
I need to call this in. No, you don't.

278
00:18:33,564 --> 00:18:35,199
不，我不能 No, I don't.

279
00:18:40,337 --> 00:18:41,871
午安，薩吉亞斯博士
Afternoon, Dr. Sagias.

280
00:18:43,607 --> 00:18:45,708
很高興見到你
It's great to see you.

281
00:18:45,775 --> 00:18:47,611
你想讓我帶團隊
Would you like me to get the team

282
00:18:47,677 --> 00:18:49,712
並到現場見你嗎？
and meet you at the site?

283
00:18:49,779 --> 00:18:51,748
沒有必要
Won't be necessary.

284
00:18:52,650 --> 00:18:54,684
好的 All right.

285
00:18:54,751 --> 00:18:56,986
聽起來不錯
Sounds good.

286
00:19:25,748 --> 00:19:28,885
我的朋友，我在監獄裡待太久了
Been in prison far too long, my friend.

287
00:19:37,727 --> 00:19:39,796
我知道你所經歷的什麼
I know what you're going through.

288
00:19:48,305 --> 00:19:50,006
等待結束了
The wait is over.

289
00:19:52,041 --> 00:19:54,078
我真不敢相信我錯過了那個
I can't believe I missed that.

290
00:19:54,144 --> 00:19:55,512
什麼? What?

291
00:19:55,579 --> 00:19:57,081
那是蘇利特
That's thulite.

292
00:19:57,147 --> 00:19:58,881
這就是為什麼它有粉紅對其着色
That's why it has that pink tint to it.

293
00:19:58,948 --> 00:20:01,518
蘇利特？是的，是挪威語
Thulite? Yeah, it's Norwegian.

294
00:20:01,585 --> 00:20:03,420
這些是巨大的岩石
These are huge rocks.

295
00:20:03,487 --> 00:20:05,089
他們在這裡幹什麼？
What are they doing here?

296
00:20:05,155 --> 00:20:06,624
他們會周遊全國
Would they travel across the country

297
00:20:06,690 --> 00:20:08,092
以成噸的蘇利特？
with tons of thulite?

298
00:20:08,158 --> 00:20:10,059
你在加州找不到蘇利特
You can't find thulite in California.

299
00:20:10,127 --> 00:20:12,529
不是一千年前 我是說，他們發現了一些東西
Not a thousand years ago. I mean, they found something

300
00:20:12,596 --> 00:20:14,531
與塞爾湖相似，但很深
similar at Searles Lake, but deep.

301
00:20:14,598 --> 00:20:17,534
真的很深-你需要19世紀的工程
Really deep-you'd need 19th century engineering

302
00:20:17,601 --> 00:20:20,337
來粹取它 嘿，崔博士
to extract it. Hey, Dr. Choi.

303
00:20:20,404 --> 00:20:22,339
早上好，哈樂德
Morning, Harold.

304
00:20:22,406 --> 00:20:23,973
薩吉亞斯說他今天要來嗎？
Did Sagias say he was coming in today?

305
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:26,510
沒有，我剛剛和他通了電話 為什麼？
No, I just spoke to him on the phone. Why?

306
00:20:26,577 --> 00:20:28,811
我很確定他在這裡
I'm pretty sure he's here.

307
00:20:28,878 --> 00:20:30,913
什麼? 我想他在墳墓裡
What? I think he's in the tomb.

308
00:20:30,980 --> 00:20:33,684


309
00:20:33,751 --> 00:20:35,286
你授權使用炸藥了嗎？
Did you authorize the explosives?

310
00:20:35,352 --> 00:20:38,355
我為什麼要這麼做？哈樂德，打911
Why would I do that? Harold, call 911.

311
00:20:41,858 --> 00:20:43,960
尼克? 哈囉? 
Nick? Hello?

312
00:20:44,027 --> 00:20:46,497
格雷斯，我覺得房間變大了
Grace, I think the room got bigger.

313
00:20:46,563 --> 00:20:47,765
另一扇門開了！
Another door opened!

314
00:20:47,830 --> 00:20:49,233
尼克! 哇，哇，哇！
Nick! Whoa, whoa, whoa!

315
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:51,669
有很多氫氣！我們應該在外面等
It's a lot of hydrogen! We should wait outside.

316
00:20:51,735 --> 00:20:53,504
聽著，我猜這次是
Listen, my guess is this time

317
00:20:53,570 --> 00:20:56,806
有一個揮發性的化學反應
there was a volatile chemical reaction.

318
00:20:56,873 --> 00:20:58,676
另一扇門 誰在乎呢？走吧！
Another door. Who cares? Let's go!

319
00:20:58,742 --> 00:21:00,177
我們在找尼克
We're looking for Nick.

320
00:21:00,244 --> 00:21:02,146
不，這是一個剛剛爆炸的不穩定地點
No, this is a volatile site that just exploded

321
